docs.abstract: This week we celebrate the victory of Google’s computer AI with a simple strategy challenge.

docs.abstract: IBM has bought four companies since it created Watson Health last April, gaining data on millions of patients that it will use to try to improve care.
docs.snippet: IBM has bought four companies since it created Watson Health last April, gaining data on millions of patients that it will use to try to improve care.
docs.lead_paragraph: IBM is looking to enhance the growth of its Watson Health business with the $2.6 billion purchase of Truven Health Analytics, which has data on the cost and treatment of more than 200 million patients.

headline.main: IBM Buys Truven for $2.6 Billion, Adding to Trove of Patient Data

docs.abstract: Five years after a computer won “Jeopardy,” excitement over A.I. is at a peak, but the commercial potential of the achievement will take some years to be realized.
